Q:2:-Describe the significance of the Turing Test and why it is still relevant today.
Ans: The test was proposed by Alan Turng in 1950, to check that whether a machine can mimic human intelligence so accurately that a person can not distinguish that whether it is a machine or a person. Even today it is significant because it can be used to measure conversational AI's capabilities.

